Q2. Roles and Responsibilities
Role	Team / Title	Key Responsibilities
Incident Commander	IT Manager / CISO	Overall leader. Declares the incident, approves containment steps, manages the big picture, and ensures resources are available.
Security Analyst	Security Operations (SOC)	Investigator. Analyzes logs, identifies the root cause, tracks the attacker’s actions, and recommends containment/eradication steps.
Forensic Lead	IT Forensics / Security	Evidence Collector. Preserves forensic images, maintains chain of custody for legal purposes, and performs deep-dive analysis.
IT/Operations	Systems / Network Admin	Implementer. Executes containment (e.g., blocking IPs, isolating systems), patches vulnerabilities, and restores services from backups.
Communications Lead	PR / Corporate Comms	Spokesperson. Manages internal updates for employees and external statements for customers/media. Only this person speaks officially.
Legal & HR	Legal Counsel / HR	Risk Managers. Legal advises on breach notification laws and liability. HR manages internal investigations if an employee is involved.
Executive Sponsor	CIO / CEO	Decision Maker. Approves high-impact decisions (e.g., shutting down major systems, notifying law enforcement) and allocates budget.
